# ============================================================
# §1 — BACKEND (LOCKED)
# ============================================================

## 1.1 Core
- Framework: Laravel 12 (PHP 8.3+)
- Database: PostgreSQL ONLY
- Cache/Queue: Redis + Horizon
- Architecture: Event-driven (Outbox pattern)
- Storage: S3-compatible disk (MinIO in dev → AWS S3 in production)
- No MySQL fallback
- No SQLite in staging/production
- No local disk for production image storage

## 1.2 PHP Law
- declare(strict_types=1) mandatory on every PHP file
- Anonymous migration classes only
- Every migration MUST implement down()
- No inline SQL in controllers
- Complex queries must use Query Object pattern (ListXQuery / FindXQuery)
- Policies gate ALL controller actions
- No anonymous arrays as DTOs — use typed DTO classes or phpdoc array shapes
- No Laravel facades inside app/Domain/ or app/Application/
  → Domain: zero framework dependencies
  → Application: may use Laravel contracts only (not facades)
  → Infrastructure: only layer allowed to use facades (DB::, Storage::, etc.)

## 1.3 RBAC (Spatie)
- Use spatie/laravel-permission exclusively
- Never manually create Spatie tables
- Backend is source of truth
- Frontend may hide UI elements, but NEVER enforces security
- User model uses Spatie\Permission\Traits\HasRoles
- All policies extend app/Policies/BasePolicy.php
- BasePolicy provides isSuperAdmin() and isAdmin() helpers

## 1.4 Architecture Layers (STRICT — layer-first, not module-first)

app/
  Domain/{Module}/         ← Entities, Value Objects, business rules
                             Zero framework dependencies
  Application/{Module}/
    Commands/              ← State-changing use cases
    Queries/               ← Read-only use cases
  Infrastructure/{Module}/ ← DB persistence, external integrations
  Policies/                ← Authorization (extends BasePolicy)
  Services/                ← Cross-module coordinators (ActivityLogger, SearchService)
  Events/                  ← Domain events (past-tense naming: TaskCreated)
  Listeners/               ← Event handlers

Controllers = orchestration only (validate → call Application → return response)

NEVER create:
  app/Modules/             ← governance violation
  app/Repositories/        ← use Infrastructure/{Module}/ instead
  app/Actions/             ← use Application/Commands/ instead
  app/Helpers/             ← no magic helpers
  app/Utils/               ← no utility folders

NOTE: app/Actions/Fortify/ is vendor scaffolding created by Laravel Fortify.
      It is NOT a custom Actions layer. Do NOT delete it.



# ============================================================
# §2 — DATABASE SCHEMA (NO DRIFT — HARD LOCK)
# ============================================================

## 2.1 Primary Keys

DEFAULT:
- UUID via gen_random_uuid()

EXCEPTIONS (BIGSERIAL only):
- notifications
- activity_logs

Never:
- UUID on notifications/activity_logs
- BIGSERIAL anywhere else

---

## 2.2 Foreign Key Type Rule

- FK → users.id → foreignId()
- FK → UUID table → foreignUuid()
- Never mix types
- Never foreignUuid() to users.id

---

## 2.3 Tasks Table (STRICT LOCK)

Fields:
- id UUID PK default gen_random_uuid()
- status VARCHAR(20) CHECK ('open','in_progress','done','cancelled')
- priority VARCHAR(20) CHECK ('low','normal','high','urgent')
- due_at TIMESTAMPTZ nullable
- started_at TIMESTAMPTZ nullable
- completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ nullable
- parent_task_id UUID FK → tasks.id ON DELETE SET NULL
- created_by_user_id BIGINT FK → users.id ON DELETE SET NULL

Named Constraints:
- chk_tasks_parent_not_self
- chk_tasks_completed_requires_done
- chk_td_no_self (task_dependencies)

Forbidden:
- assigned_to_user_id
- owner_user_id
- due_date

---

## 2.4 No tenant_id (ABSOLUTE)

- No tenant_id anywhere
- No RLS
- No tenant-scoped cache keys

---

## 2.5 Polymorphic Columns (STRICT)

ID columns MUST be VARCHAR(64):
- commentable_id
- linkable_id
- entity_id
- subject_id

Type columns MUST be VARCHAR(191):
- commentable_type
- linkable_type
- entity_type
- subject_type
(191 safely stores fully-qualified class names — intentional hardening over charter VARCHAR(64))

Never:
- BIGINT
- TEXT
- UUID type for polymorphic columns

---

## 2.6 Index Placement Law

- Performance indexes via DB::statement() AFTER Schema::create()
- Never $table->index() inside Schema::create()
- $table->unique() inline is allowed (data integrity constraint, not perf index)

---

## 2.7 Required Named Indexes (EXPLICIT)

idx_ct_poly
→ comment_threads(commentable_type, commentable_id)

idx_tl_linkable
→ task_links(linkable_type, linkable_id)

idx_notif_entity
→ notifications(entity_type, entity_id)

idx_tr_task
→ task_reminders(task_id)

idx_tr_remind_at
→ task_reminders(remind_at) WHERE is_sent = false

idx_np_user
→ notification_preferences(user_id)

idx_al_causer
→ activity_logs(causer_user_id)

---

## 2.8 FK Delete Behavior (EXPLICIT)

DEFAULT → RESTRICT

CASCADE:
- project_memberships.project_id
- project_memberships.user_id
- tasks.project_id
- task_assignees.task_id
- task_assignees.user_id
- task_dependencies.task_id
- task_dependencies.depends_on_task_id
- task_reminders.task_id
- task_reminders.user_id
- task_links.task_id
- comment_participants.thread_id
- comment_participants.user_id
- comment_messages.thread_id
- notifications.user_id
- notification_preferences.user_id
- financial_snapshots.project_id
- budget_reallocations.project_id

SET NULL:
- project_memberships.assigned_by_user_id
- tasks.parent_task_id
- tasks.created_by_user_id
- task_assignees.assigned_by_user_id
- task_links.created_by_user_id
- comment_threads.created_by_user_id
- comment_threads.resolved_by_user_id
- comment_messages.parent_message_id
- comment_messages.author_user_id
- activity_logs.causer_user_id

---

## 2.9 Unique Constraint Names

- uq_np_user_type_channel
- uq_pm_project_user
- uq_ta_task_user
- uq_td_pair

---

## 2.10 Soft Deletes

Allowed:
- projects
- tasks
- comment_threads

Never:
- activity_logs
- notifications
- financial_snapshots
- budget_reallocations

---

## 2.11 Timestamps

- Always timestampTz() — never timestamp()
- Log tables (activity_logs): created_at only — no updated_at

---

## 2.12 activity_logs Column Name (LOCKED)

- Column name: causer_user_id (NOT created_by_user_id)
- Index name: idx_al_causer (NOT idx_al_actor_created)
- Matches charter §3.13 exactly



# ============================================================
# §3 — FRONTEND (LOCKED)
# ============================================================

## 3.1 Core
- React 19+
- TypeScript ONLY — no 'any' types
- Tailwind CSS v4
- shadcn/ui for all UI primitives
- lucide-react for all icons — no other icon library
- Inertia useForm() for all forms — never react-hook-form
- SweetAlert2 via resources/js/Services/confirm.ts wrapper ONLY
- Functional components only — no class components
- Import alias @/ for all internal imports

Forbidden:
- Vue
- Plain JS
- Redux
- Direct Swal.fire() calls
- Class components
- react-hook-form
- Any icon library other than lucide-react

---

## 3.2 RTL / LTR (Arabic + English) — MANDATORY

- Set dir + lang at <html> layout level ONLY
- Read dir and locale from Inertia shared props via usePage().props
- HandleInertiaRequests shares: auth.user, locale, dir
- Use Tailwind rtl: and ltr: variants for directional styles
- Typography: Inter (EN) · Cairo (AR) — loaded via CSS, not CDN in components
- Fonts declared in resources/css/fonts.css, imported in app.css

Never:
- Hardcoded dir="rtl" in any component
- Ternary dir hacks inside JSX
- Loading fonts via Google CDN inside TSX components
- Setting dir/lang per-component — layout level ONLY

---

## 3.3 Accessibility (A11Y) — REQUIRED

- Focus trap mandatory in all dialogs
- ESC must close dialogs and command palette
- Arrow navigation required in command palette
- All interactive elements must have label or aria-label
- All images must have alt text
- Thumbnails use loading="lazy"
- Keyboard listeners must clean up in useEffect return()

---

## 3.4 Global Search (Command Palette)

Shortcuts:
- macOS → Cmd+K
- Windows → Ctrl+K (DEFAULT)
- Optional alt → Ctrl+Alt+K (user-configurable only)

Rules:
- Mounted once in AppLayout — never duplicated
- Debounce ≥ 300ms
- RBAC enforced server-side
- Soft-deleted records excluded
- PostgreSQL FTS only (tsvector + GIN index)
- No LIKE '%term%' on large tables
- Keyboard listener must use useEffect with cleanup on unmount
- Result format: { type, title, subtitle?, route } per SEARCH_ARCHITECTURE.md §6

---

## 3.5 Enterprise DataTable (MANDATORY)

All index pages MUST support:
- Server-side pagination
- Global search
- Column search
- Column filters
- Show/Hide columns (persisted per user per module)
- Row selection
- Bulk actions
- Excel export (server-side)
- PDF export (server-side)
- Loading / Empty / Error states

Server MUST:
- Re-validate every selected_id against policy
- Reject unauthorized IDs silently
- Log bulk actions in activity_logs
- Log exports in activity_logs

Never:
- Client-side filtering of full dataset
- Static HTML tables
- Duplicate DataTable logic per module

---

## 3.6 SweetAlert2

Allowed only for:
- Destructive confirmations (delete, bulk delete)
- Critical blocking alerts

Never use for:
- Forms
- Complex modals
- Image preview

MUST use wrapper at resources/js/Services/confirm.ts:
  confirmDelete(message: string): Promise<boolean>
  confirmAction(title: string, message: string): Promise<boolean>

Never call Swal.fire() directly anywhere in the codebase.

---

## 3.7 Modal & Toast

- Single modal system: shadcn Dialog only
- Single toast system: shadcn Toaster (Sonner) via AppToaster.tsx
- Both mounted once in AppLayout
- Focus trap mandatory in modals
- ESC closes modals



# ============================================================
# §4 — IMAGE & MEDIA (FORENSIC GRADE)
# ============================================================

## 4.1 Client Pipeline
- Crop (react-easy-crop)
- Resize (max 2000px longest side)
- Compress (quality 0.80–0.85)
- Deterministic rename before upload

## 4.2 Server Pipeline
1. Validate MIME via finfo (never trust file extension)
2. Normalize EXIF orientation BEFORE stripping
3. Strip all EXIF metadata
4. Convert to WebP
5. Resize to max 2000px
6. Generate 300×300 square thumbnail
7. Compute SHA256 for deduplication
8. Store full image + thumbnail
9. Write record to platform_files
10. Attach via file_attachments polymorphic pivot

## 4.3 Storage
- Disk: S3-compatible (MinIO in dev, AWS S3 in production)
- Laravel config: filesystems.disks.s3
- Env: AWS_ENDPOINT=http://minio:9000 (dev)
- Path: {bucket}/{entity}/{entity_id}/{field}/{YYYY}/{MM}/{DD}/
- Naming: {entity}_{id}_{field}_{timestamp}.webp

## 4.4 Required Components
- resources/js/Components/Media/ImageUploader.tsx
- resources/js/Components/Media/ImageThumb.tsx
- resources/js/Components/Media/ImageLightbox.tsx

Never:
- Store raw user filename
- Accept SVG uploads (XSS vector)
- Skip EXIF stripping
- Show full-size images in list views
- Use raw <img> for uploaded content
- Use raw file input outside ImageUploader
- Store MinIO/S3 credentials in source code



# ============================================================
# §5 — PERFORMANCE GUARDS
# ============================================================

- Default pagination: 15–25 rows
- Max per_page: 100 (enforced in FilterDTO.fromRequest())
- Debounce search input ≥ 300ms
- Virtualize lists with > 200 rows
- Disable submit button during processing (prevent double-submit)
- Show loading indicator on Inertia route change
- Never fetch full dataset to client for filtering



# ============================================================
# §6 — AI CONTRACT
# ============================================================

Optional method on any model:
  public function toAIContext(): array;

Defined in: app/Domain/Shared/Contracts/HasAIContext.php

Rules:
- Must pass policy check before calling
- No raw Eloquent model dumps
- No cost breakdowns or margin percentages
- No internal-only financial formulas
- Return phpdoc-typed shape:
  @return array<string, scalar|array<string, mixed>|bool|null>



# ============================================================
# §7 — VERIFICATION (BEFORE SCHEMA COMMIT)
# ============================================================

Run /.cursor/scripts/verify_governance.sh before every schema commit.

7 required checks:
1. tasks.id is UUID
2. No assigned_to_user_id on tasks
3. notifications.id is BIGSERIAL (not UUID)
4. Zero tenant_id columns anywhere
5. uq_np_user_type_channel exists
6. chk_td_no_self exists
7. All 6 required named indexes exist

Additional:
- All polymorphic *_id = VARCHAR(64)
- All polymorphic *_type = VARCHAR(191)
- No foreignUuid() pointing to users.id
- causer_user_id in activity_logs (not created_by_user_id)
- softDeletes only on: projects, tasks, comment_threads



# ============================================================
# §8 — FORBIDDEN PATTERNS
# ============================================================

DATABASE:
- tenant_id in any table
- foreignUuid() referencing users.id
- Missing down() in any migration
- Inline SQL in controllers
- $table->index() inside Schema::create()
- timestamp() instead of timestampTz()
- softDeletes on: activity_logs, notifications, financial_snapshots, budget_reallocations

ARCHITECTURE:
- app/Modules/ (use layer-first: Domain/Application/Infrastructure)
- Custom app/Actions/ layer (use Application/Commands/ instead)
  NOTE: app/Actions/Fortify/ is vendor scaffolding — do NOT delete it
- app/Repositories/ as standalone layer (use Infrastructure/{Module}/)
- app/Helpers/ or app/Utils/
- Laravel facades inside app/Domain/ or app/Application/
- Scaffolding a module without a verified charter migration
- Business logic in controllers
- Cross-layer shortcuts (Domain calling Infrastructure directly)

FRONTEND:
- Vue, plain JS, Redux
- Direct Swal.fire() — use confirm.ts only
- Static HTML tables — use DataTable component
- Multiple modal systems (shadcn Dialog only)
- Multiple toast systems (AppToaster only)
- Multiple search/command palette instances
- react-hook-form (use Inertia useForm() only)
- Icons from any library other than lucide-react
- Hardcoded dir="rtl" in components
- Fonts loaded via CDN inside TSX components

IMAGES:
- Raw <img> for uploaded content (use ImageThumb / ImageLightbox)
- Raw file input outside ImageUploader
- SVG uploads
- Skipping EXIF stripping
- Full-size images in list views
- Local disk for production storage
- Credentials hardcoded in source code
